column2: "What a coincidence meeting you here, partner. Are you looking for something?"
"Little shadows? Why would you be looking for those?"
"If you're looking for them, I think I saw one over there."
"I'm the kind of person that finds things for other people, but never for myself."
"I think it was over here. Looks like it's gone already."
"It's not like guard mechs would have this. Maybe the shadow dropped it?"
"Well, you may not have found them, but you definitely found proof they exist."
"To be honest, there are too many things we don't know abut this planet anyway."
"Call it intuition or a gut feeling, but I get the sense there are more mysteries we haven't even uncovered yet."
"I guess we'll just have to figure it out as we go."
"Okay, I'm going to get back to searching."
"Partner, maybe next time you can help me with one of my quests. Later!"
